  <text xml:id="L_08-02-091-000_text">
    <body xml:id="Document">
      <div type="chapter" xml:id="Ch91" n="91">
        <pb type="VIII_2" n="729"/>
        <head>91. DE HOROLOGIIS PENDULIS, NON TAM AEQUALIBUS QUAM CREDUNTUR</head>
        <head>[April – Mai 1673]</head>
        <div type="ueberlieferung">
          <p><hi rendition="#b #smaller">Überlieferung:</hi><listWit>
              <witness><msDesc>
                  <msIdentifier>
                    <repository>Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz Bibliothek Hannover</repository>
                    <idno type="Signatur"/>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                    <summary><p>Konzept: LH XXXVIII Bl. 170-171. 1 Bog. 4<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>, beschnitten. 2 S. auf Bl. 170. Bl. 171 r<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>
                        überliefert N. 90. Bl. 171 v<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi> ist leer.</p><p>Cc
                        2, Nr. 00</p></summary>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                    <objectDesc form="Handschrift" corresp="L_objectDesc.xml#handschrift"/>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                    <origin/>
                  </history>
                </msDesc></witness>
            </listWit></p>
        </div>
        <div type="contents">
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p4"><hi rendition="#smaller"><hi rendition="#b">Datierungsgründe</hi>: Das
              vorliegende Stück N. 91 nimmt auf Christiaan Huygens’ <ref corresp="#bib_00123"/><hi rendition="#i">Horologium oscillatorium</hi> bezug. Ein druckfrisches Exemplar
              dieser Abhandlung bekam Leibniz wahrscheinlich Anfang April 1673 geschenkt, als er
              Huygens in Paris besuchte. Seine Randbemerkungen darin sowie mannigfaltige Hinweise in
              mathematischen Aufzeichnungen zeigen, dass er sich noch in den Monaten April und Mai
              1673 mit dem <ref corresp="#bib_00123"/><hi rendition="#i">Horologium
                oscillatorium</hi> auseinandergesetzt hat. (Siehe hierüber <ref corresp="#bib_00262"/><hi rendition="#i">LSB</hi> VII, 4 N. 2, S. 27.) Auch N. 91 dürfte in diesem
              Zeitraum entstanden sein, wie dies insbesondere aus dem Incipit hervorgeht.</hi></p>
        </div>
        <div type="text">
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p5" rendition="#noindent"><pb type="L"/><fw type="folNum">[170 r<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>]</fw></p>
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p6" rendition="#c">De Horologiis pendulis, non tam aequalibus quam
            creduntur</p>
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p7" rendition="#noindent">Cum nuper Horologia pendula diligentius
            considerassem et a cl. <app type="Cfootnote">
              <lem type="main">Hugenio<index indexName="Namensregister">
                  <term><hi rendition="#g">Huygens</hi> (Hugenius, Ugenius, Hugens, Huguens),
                    Christiaan 1629-1695</term>
                </index></lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">Hugenio</note>
              <note type="editorial"><bibl corresp="#bib_00123"><hi rendition="#k">C. Huygens</hi>,
                    <hi rendition="#i">Horologium oscillatorium</hi>, Amsterdam 1673, S. 6 (<hi rendition="#i">HO</hi> XVIII, S. 95).</bibl></note>
            </app>
            <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">fol. 6.</add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> asseri animadvertissem, tantam esse eorum aequalitatem, ut <hi rendition="#i">vel
              recte tempus metiantur, vel omnino non metiantur</hi>; ita, ut jactatio navis proinde
            non noceat, modo <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">motus non interruptus</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">motus</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" cause="addition"><note type="editorial">|</note> <add>non</add>
                <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg.</hi> |</note> interruptus <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> servetur; hoc quia mihi permirum videbatur, quaesivi an alicubi demonstrasset.
            Cumque nuspiam ab eo id probari viderem, magnus enim pulcherrimarum <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">sane</add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> demonstrationum apparatus tantum oscillationum spontanearum a sola descendentis
            gravitate ortarum <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">isochronismum ostendit;</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">isochronismum</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> probat </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> ostendit; <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> in rem hanc <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">inquisivi curatius,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">inquisivi</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> diligentius </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> curatius, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> tandemque aliud <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">plane</add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> dicendum deprehendi.</p>
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p8">Ponamus Pendulum ex aliquo puncto ut <hi rendition="#i">A</hi> libere
            solo suo pondere demissum oscillationes aliquot <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">peragere, ut <formula xml:id="Ch91.p8.m1">
                  <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>D</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:math>
                </formula>
                <formula xml:id="Ch91.p8.m2">
                  <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>B</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>E</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:math>
                </formula> easque concedamus (ob cycloides eas) esse isochronas,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">peragere,</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> eas </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> ut <hi rendition="#i">AD</hi>, <hi rendition="#i">BE</hi>, easque <app>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="a">esse isochronas </rdg>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="b" cause="addition">concedamus (ob cycloides <note type="editorial">|</note> <add>eas</add>
                    <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg.</hi> |</note> ) esse isochronas,
                      <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
                </app></rdg>
            </app> nulla resistentiae aeris erga penetrationem, aut fili contra flexionem, aut axis
            contra gyrationem in polis, habita ratione, modo vi solius gravitatis moveatur.</p>
          <pb type="VIII_2" n="730"/>
          <figure rendition="#own-line_centered" xml:id="Ch91.fig1_1">
            <graphic url="./images/lh038_170v.svg" style="trim:  -3mm 3mm -13mm 0mm; clip: true" width="164.7756pt" xml:id="Ch91.g1"/>
            <head xml:id="Ch91.fig1_2" style="; text-align:center">[<hi rendition="#i">Fig.
              1</hi>]</head>
          </figure>
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p9" rendition="#noindent">Nunc vero ponamus pendulum ex puncto <hi rendition="#i">A</hi> initio libere demissum vi solius quidem gravitatis <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">moveri coepisse,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">moveri</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" cause="deletion"><note type="editorial">|</note> <del>facile</del>
                <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">gestr.</hi> |</note> coepisse, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> sed durantibus oscillationibus cum ex <hi rendition="#i">B</hi> nisu <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">gravitatis descendere inciperet,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">gravitatis</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> descendens pervenisset in <hi rendition="#i">C</hi>
              </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> descendere inciperet, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> ibi accipere ictum a rota horologii, ac proinde majori celeritate descensum
            continuare quam alias fecisset eoque motu non excurrere tantum usque ad <hi rendition="#i">E</hi>, sed altius adhuc usque ad <hi rendition="#i">G</hi>.</p>
          <p xml:id="Ch91.p10">Porro si impetus a rota impressus non sit nimius (quod utique caveri
            potest ac debet) tunc utique <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">assumi
                poterit</add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> alia oscillatio <hi rendition="#i">FG</hi> talis, ut pendulum ex puncto <hi rendition="#i">F</hi> (recte ad hoc assumto) demissum, libere nisu gravitatis eandem
            collegisset celeritatem, ubi venisset in <hi rendition="#i">B</hi>, quam nunc ibi <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">acquisivit <pb type="L"/><fw type="folNum">[170 v<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>]</fw> impetu rotae impresso.</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">acquisivit</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> partim <pb type="L"/><fw type="folNum">[170 v<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>]</fw> descensu a <formula xml:id="Ch91.p10.m1">
                  <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
                    <m:mi>B</m:mi>
                  </m:math>
                </formula> ad <formula xml:id="Ch91.p10.m2">
                  <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
                    <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                  </m:math>
                </formula>, partim </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> impetu rotae impresso. <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> Et proinde vi hujus oscillationis pendulum etiam necessario pervenisset usque
              <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">ad <hi rendition="#i">G</hi>, eadem enim vis</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">ad <hi rendition="#i">G</hi>,</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> cum eadem </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> eadem enim <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> quam pendulum habet <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">in <hi rendition="#i">B</hi> eodemque tendens undecunque orta ipsum
                eodem</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">in <hi rendition="#i">B</hi></note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> undecunque orta <app>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="a">ipsum eodem </rdg>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="b">eodemque tendens, </rdg>
                </app></rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> eodemque <seg type="apparat-ellipsis"/> eodem <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> elevabit, nempe in <hi rendition="#i">G</hi>. Haec oscillatio <hi rendition="#i">FG</hi> utique erit aequidiuturna oscillationi spontaneae <hi rendition="#i">BE</hi>
            vel <hi rendition="#i">AD</hi>. Sed <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">eadem <hi rendition="#i">FG</hi> diuturnior</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">eadem</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> longior </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> <hi rendition="#i">FG</hi> diuturnior <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> esset parte sui <hi rendition="#i">BG</hi>, quae cum sit aequidiuturna
            oscillationi praesenti <hi rendition="#i">BG</hi> quae ab impetu rotae <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">gravitati
                  accedente</add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> orta est, sequitur oscillationem <hi rendition="#i">FG</hi>, adeoque et
            oscillationem <hi rendition="#i">AD</hi> vel <hi rendition="#i">BE</hi> diuturniorem
            esse oscillatione <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L"><hi rendition="#i">BG</hi></add></lem>
              <note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note>
            </app> orta ab impetu rotae gravitati accedente, ac proinde oscillationes ab
            inaequalibus impressionibus rotarum horologii, aut jactationum navis, aliisque hujusmodi
            causis reddi inaequales. Quod demonstrandum sumseramus. Itaque quo <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">major in pendulis obtineatur aequalitas,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">major</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> pendulis <app>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="a">detur </rdg>
                  <rdg wit="#L" n="b">inaequalitatis </rdg>
                </app></rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> in pendulis obtineatur aequalitas, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> adhibendum erit praeterea artificium meum, <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">quo efficitur,</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">quo</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> alternis </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> efficitur, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> ut impetus pendulo vel elastro, eorumve libramento impressus sit semper idem.
            Machina Horologii pondus aliquod vel Elastrum exiguum, tantisper <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">dum libramentum</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">dum</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> pendulum </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> libramentum <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> vibratur restituente, ut <app type="Bfootnote">
              <lem type="main">postea ad rediens libramentum, novo ictu priorem aequante
                percutiendum sit paratum.</lem>
              <note type="lemma-abbrev">postea</note>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="1"> rediens libramentum paratum </rdg>
              <rdg wit="#L" n="2"> ad rediens <seg type="apparat-ellipsis"/> paratum. <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg>
            </app> Ex his ratio redditur ejus quod ipse fatetur Hugenius,<index indexName="Namensregister">
              <term><hi rendition="#g">Huygens</hi>, Christiaan (1629-1695)</term>
            </index> quo minore vi pendula motum continuare possunt, eo esse exactiora; quod non
            esset, si vis impressa non turbaret.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
